{"type":"text","timestamp":1781756239195,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff808ffewqP1i1p6C1RaMp","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f29cfe001NmTf8kWTslHrs9","messageID":"msg_ed8f22312001ArrTiQ9e0272Co","sessionID":"ses_1270ff808ffewqP1i1p6C1RaMp","type":"text","text":"I found one likely spec-alignment defect to record: `processBatches` checks `shouldAbort` at batch start, but still unconditionally waits the inter-batch delay after a cancellation becomes true during the previous batch. The spec claims cancellation skips remaining batches and their pacing delay.","time":{"start":1781756239102,"end":1781756239193},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0547c97333a51a62016a33714f10f08191a8731c12b0f5444a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
